1. npm run build: build dev main.js, then localhost can run with this main.js

2. npm run watch: watch and build dev main.js if source file changed, refresh browser to reflect new change

3. npm run hotwatch: with node backend running, hot-reloading new change

4. npm run build-prod: build prod dist/main-[#hash].js

5. Using Webpack transparently with Django + hot reloading React components as a bonus
	* http://owaislone.org/blog/webpack-plus-reactjs-and-django/
	* webpack-dev-server react-hot-loader two packages for hot-reload
